1. Make sure OpenGL is installed on your OS, usually it comes pre-installed.
See http://www.opengl.org/wiki/Getting_started

2. Install Haskell (GHC compiler and libraries) via one of the following procedures
	a. Download and install Haskell Platform from http://hackage.haskell.org/platform/
	b. Install haskell-platform from your OS package manager like yum, brew, etc.

3. Run cabal install from this directory. It compiles and installs program in a user directory 
specific to your OS. Last line of install output tells you which directory it is actually stored in.
$ cabal install

4. Run installed program
$ <installed-path>/MongoShardingSim

5. Click anywhere on window that pops up to see help
